{"id": "EUVD-2022-55478", "enisaUuid": "7a8a9a3e-ba8e-30b6-8d38-b91f39f4f4c6", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nfuse: write inode in fuse_release()\n\nA race between write(2) and close(2) allows pages to be dirtied after\nfuse_flush -> write_inode_now().  If these pages are not flushed from\nfuse_release(), then there might not be a writable open file later.  So any\nremaining dirty pages must be written back before the file is released.\n\nThis is a partial revert of the blamed commit.", "datePublished": "2025-06-18T12:30:56", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-19T15:31:31", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5ccb0420b7c9334ab8122037847101931b899301", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4bd9d5d20f344d015422969302d12653c903c271", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/035ff33cf4db101250fb980a3941bf078f37a544", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50217"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50217"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "1137a9e4-e302-3321-a9fd-8bd9a1fa9565", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.18.18"}, {"id": "39cd239a-1bef-33da-b64e-3c8181cdd3da", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19.2"}, {"id": "4d3381ad-92ad-350b-9317-5719aa779d30", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "36ea23374d1f7b6a9d96a2b61d38830fdf23e45d <5ccb0420b7c9334ab8122037847101931b899301"}, {"id": "5043f596-adb6-3456-b6a8-db791333bdea", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "76d222ee-f5d2-339e-a740-dd86d657634a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0"}, {"id": "7e6fae34-e07e-3977-8be1-383342c0a1bc", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.16"}, {"id": "90b738c4-c43a-306c-b302-ef546c3091da", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "36ea23374d1f7b6a9d96a2b61d38830fdf23e45d <4bd9d5d20f344d015422969302d12653c903c271"}, {"id": "afec90c2-ae27-3266-9c1a-7f5857dd40ea", "product"